body: Hey  I want to work on the issue. Could you please elaborate more on this what exactly to be done?

@shraddhafalane Thanks! We can make a change like this:

```diff
diff --git a/mlflow/sklearn/utils.py b/mlflow/sklearn/utils.py
index 604407112..656faf092 100644
--- a/mlflow/sklearn/utils.py
+++ b/mlflow/sklearn/utils.py
@@ -553,6 +553,24 @@ def _log_specialized_estimator_content(
     return metrics
 
 
+def _log_estimator_html(run_id, estimator):
+    from sklearn.utils import estimator_html_repr
+
+    # Set charset to prevent the triangle toggle buttons from being garbled
+    estimator_html = f"""
+<!DOCTYPE html>
+<html lang="en">
+  <head>
+    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
+  </head>
+  <body>
+    {estimator_html_repr.estimator_html_repr(estimator)}
+  </body>
+</html>
+"""
+    MlflowClient().log_text(run_id, estimator_html, artifact_file="estimator.html")
+
+
 def _log_estimator_content(
     autologging_client,
     estimator,
@@ -614,6 +632,8 @@ def _log_estimator_content(
             autologging_client.log_metrics(run_id=run_id, metrics={score_key: score})
             metrics[score_key] = score
 
+    _log_estimator_html(run_id, estimator)
     return metrics
```

We should add a test like this:

```diff
diff --git a/tests/sklearn/test_sklearn_autolog.py b/tests/sklearn/test_sklearn_autolog.py
index b71cb3a81..59b6cc101 100644
--- a/tests/sklearn/test_sklearn_autolog.py
+++ b/tests/sklearn/test_sklearn_autolog.py
@@ -2103,3 +2103,11 @@ def test_autolog_emits_warning_message_when_pos_label_used_for_multilabel():
             "Metric error: Target is multiclass but average='binary'. Please choose another "
             "average setting, one of [None, 'micro', 'macro', 'weighted']."
         )
+
+
+def test_estimator_html_is_logged():
+    mlflow.sklearn.autolog()
+    with mlflow.start_run() as run:
+        sklearn.svm.SVC().fit(*get_iris())
+        artifacts = get_run_data(run.info.run_id)[3]
+        assert "estimator.html" in artifacts

```
